<br>
Me.  I ALWAYS have Rune III on.  I would imagine I will soon (probably in the next level or two) get to the point where Rune III doesn't last more than one or two smacks, and then perhaps I'll move to Rune V, because hopefully by then I'll be getting cash/items/gems from dungeons enough to cover it.<br>
I'll Rune a puller for a particularly big pull.<br>
I'll rune the cleric/healer if he/she's getting beaten on.<br>
I'll rune anyone who gets below 1.5 bubbles of life and looks like they're still getting hit, and I have the mana for it.<br>
<br>
As for money items:  I really don't expect much, if anything, if I'm doing Rune III's.  They're cheap, and I usually make what I spent+a little by the mere cash split alone.<br>
<br>
Raids:<br>
<br>
Me.  Again, I always keep Rune III on.  Even with Rune V, now, I'll prbably continue to do Rune III, although perhaps I'll experiment a bit on the second floor of Hate.<br>
<br>
For bosses, demis, etc, I'll do Rune V from now on for everyone.  Rune IV never seemed worth it.  Now that I'm 52, V will be great.<br>
Hell, it's around an extra 700hp!<br>
<br>
As for money items:  Again, with Rune III, I really don't give a damn if I don't get anything.  40pp spent for the chance to be on a raid is worth it.<br>
However, almost all raids I've been on I've gotten either cash or gems simply for casting Rune III, and it's usually enough or even more than enough to offset the cost.<br>
Rune V will be a different story. <p><center><img src = http://members.bellatlantic.net/~mezner/daeonsig2.jpg><br>
