nd really, 10.5 plat x 4 is obtainable by spending half an hour soloing high greens for no effort.<br>
<br>
In Goshan's case, as often as possible a level 60 enc will be dictating some nearby mob to add damage (and a lot of damage...) towards the ubermob in question. If Goshan dies, there is now some level 50-55ish mob running around killing off your raid members, and that's a bad thing. If you're not charming though, I honestly think the enc dying is a good thing. The first time I killed ixiblat, I tashed too early, and he meleed me down in fairly fast order. but I gave the tank (and the tank's cleric) a short respite from melee damage by being PUMMELED for 2 melee rounds. that's 2500ish damage I just healed the main tank :P This is not applicable in all situations, but if I see the outcome is coming close and I don't have any important job (such as charm, and in most cases in the low 50's we don't really  have anything to do during ubermobs) I will not hesitate to throw myself in the way for a few melee rounds. I have a theory that I can help vs these mobs by berserker/bedlam'ing myself, and getting the mob to aggro me for one melee round, recasting and repeating (although note, even casting these spells on yourself will cause major aggro. I've died against some ubermob once because after being beat to about 30% hp, I runed or berserkered myself just as a precaution and got a smack in the teeth for it. Unless you're playing at a meat shield, try to avoid doing this. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If the mob isn't hitting you, you can just not do anything and he'll continue to not hit you.<br>
<br>
